abstract: The female lawmaker’s purse or bag has become an outwardly physical manifestation of the nation’s evolving legislative body.
snippet: The female lawmaker’s purse or bag has become an outwardly physical manifestation of the nation’s evolving legislative body.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Amy Klobuchar, Democrat of Minnesota, was sitting in her large, sunny office recently, riffling through the contents of her black leather purse.

abstract: Senator Kirsten E. Gillibrand is leading a bipartisan group of women in a fierce battle to change attitudes about sexual crimes in the military and the legal system used to address them.
snippet: Senator Kirsten E. Gillibrand is leading a bipartisan group of women in a fierce battle to change attitudes about sexual crimes in the military and the legal system used to address them.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Shocking the gridlocked Congress into action, a half dozen or so bipartisan female senators are escalating their war on sexual crimes in the military and deploying their outrage, clout and legions of supporters against a rigid military structure and its male-dominated ranks.

snippet: Emily's List, one of the largest political action committees in the United States, is working to put the first woman in the White House.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Momentum to elect more women to high office, specifically to break the ultimate glass ceiling and elect a woman as president in the United States, has gone into high gear here with Emily’s List’s Madam President campaign, a fund-raising drive that in just a few weeks has gained thousands of new followers and thousands of dollars in donations.

abstract: President Obama’s choice to be transportation secretary, Mayor Anthony Foxx of Charlotte, N.C., zipped through a confirmation hearing on Wednesday before the Senate Commerce, Science and Transportation Committee.
snippet: President Obama’s choice to be transportation secretary, Mayor Anthony Foxx of Charlotte, N.C., zipped through a confirmation hearing on Wednesday before the Senate Commerce, Science and Transportation Committee.
lead_paragraph: President Obama’s choice to be transportation secretary, Mayor Anthony Foxx of Charlotte, N.C., zipped through a confirmation hearing on Wednesday before the Senate Commerce, Science and Transportation Committee. He was questioned on many points but pushed to make promises on nothing more than working cooperatively with Congress, putting safety first, trying to maintain air traffic control tower staffing, and visiting the site of the recent commuter train accident in Bridgeport, Conn.
